President Uhuru Kenyatta has assented to the Fisheries Management and Conservation Bill that will regulate import and export of fish.The Bill will also tame stealing of Kenya marine resources by foreigners.The President signed the Bill on Saturday after commissioning the second container terminal in Mombasa.The new law will protect marine resources and endangered fish species.It also outlaws dumping of objects that could harm fish and other marine organisms, in the sea. email print email print The terminal was constructed with funding from the Japanese government. Job boycott should be suspended to allow room for talks this week, judge rules. There are 32 million chicken in the country that are at risk of contracting the avian flu.